properties.name: Readin Ritin Rithmetic
properties.description:
The halls will soon be empty. The final bells will ring. The books will be placed on the shelf, not to be touched again until fall. Yes, the school year is almost over and soon the kids will be outside playing.

On The Passage, we play outside every week. Yet we are also learning, approaching the city streets with open eyes and open minds. We are curious. But there are some things that one learns best in a classroom environment. So this week, before the academic year draws to a close, we seek instruction at school -- several schools, in fact.

BYO pencils and books; we'll see if we can wrangle up some teachers to give us dirty looks.
